Boil a full #kettle{}. Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} into thirds, cutting any thick stems lengthways. Peel and grate your @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, stir in the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @boiled water{240%ml} into the saucepan. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken thigh{190%g}, @mixed peppers and red onion{300%g}(cut into strips) and the @Chermoula spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir to combine.

Fry until the peppers and onion have softened and the chicken is golden brown and cooked through, ~{10%minutes}. Stir occasionally and lower the heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the Tenderstem® to the pan and stir-fry for ~{2%minutes}, then add a splash of @water{}.

Pop a lid on the pan, or cover in some #foil{}. Cook until tender, a further ~{3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the bulgur is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{}.

Stir through the @harissa paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder).

Add the harissa bulgur to the chicken and veg pan, then gently mix together until combined.

Spoon the chicken and veg bulgur into your #bowls{}.

Finish with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}.

Enjoy!